{"key":"processedPost-11790099","value":{"id":11790099,"first":11788742,"last":11790334,"when":1262986347,"utime":"01/08/10 11:32 PM","content":"Sterlite and Rubbermaid are the two quality brands.&nbsp; Walmart probably has some crappy made in china totes that are brittle and is why so many people crack them while drilling the holes.<br />Use a sharp drill bit, drill at high speed, and back off on the pressure just as the bit is breaking through the plastic.&nbsp; If you have one of those brittle totes, try putting a light bulb or hair dryer inside for a few minutes to warm it up.&nbsp; That should soften the plastic and help prevent cracking.&nbsp; however, if it cracks, it's no biggie other than looks.<br />Drill holes on all six sides, and elevate the tub on bricks or some other spacer for best results.&nbsp; <br />Just to correct a technical error above, CO2 does not drain out the bottom.&nbsp; Generally, fresh air enters the bottom, passes through the perlite, and then out the sides and top.&nbsp; The CO2 mixes with the air, thus it exhausts out the sides and top.&nbsp; It's not a separate layer below the air.<br />RR","title":"Re: First Time: Shotgun Terrarium Question"}}